definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)
to pull up/to pull out/to draw out by suction/to select/to pick/to stand out (above level)/to surpass/to seize

sentences.english: Let us have a look at New Jersey's pre-eminent University Town.
sentences.chinese: 让我们看看新泽西出类拔萃的大学城。

sentences.english: I wish you every success in the future, You are worthysuccess.
sentences.chinese: 我祝你来日事业成功，出类拔萃，成功当之无愧。

sentences.english: For example: He [father] sent John to the university and was eager to have him distinguish himself.
sentences.chinese: 他送约翰上大学，巴望能让儿子出类拔萃。

sentences.english: Aileen stands out for her incredible versatility as an actress.
sentences.chinese: 艾琳多才多艺，是一位出类拔萃的女演员。

sentences.english: In this field he is facile princeps, and has left all competitors behind.
sentences.chinese: 在这方面，他是出类拔萃的，使其他的竞争者。

sentences.english: Two CEO biogs stand out from the crowd.
sentences.chinese: 有两家公司执行长的个人小传出类拔萃。

sentences.english: Quality embodies dignity, An outstanding quality will not embrace any sort of mediocrity .
sentences.chinese: 品质体现尊严，出类拔萃的品质气绝平庸。

sentences.english: Every day you have the chance to excel, to stand out, and to be exceptional.
sentences.chinese: 每天你都有机会胜人一筹，干得出色，出类拔萃。

sentences.english: When I told him that i had superlatively technical skills, he simply gave me a horse laugh.
sentences.chinese: 当我告诉他我的技术出类拔萃时，他不相信地笑了。

sentences.english: This is for Plato, the political passion par excellence.
sentences.chinese: 那就是柏拉图所谓的激情，出类拔萃的政治激情。

sentences.english: Reading great poets, I walked day and night in the shadow of excellence.
sentences.chinese: 常读大诗人的作品，朝朝夕夕走在出类拔萃的影子里。

sentences.english: From the beginning, it was evident that this boy was to be drawn to writing and the sound of words.
sentences.chinese: 这个孩子从一开始就表现出对写作和声韵的出类拔萃。

sentences.english: Professor Jao is also highly accomplished in the realm of the arts.
sentences.chinese: 饶教授在艺术领域亦取得出类拔萃的成就。

definition: top-notch (colloquial)/to push oneself to the front
erhua variant of 拔尖[ba2 jian1]
to stand out from one's fellows/high-level examination for official candidacy (traditional)
erhua variant of 頂尖|顶尖[ding3 jian1]
reckoned to be first or second best (idiom)/one of the very best/to list one by one
